SubmitterDescription.SubmitterName: International Standards For Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium (ISCA)

SampleDescription.Description: A partial chromosome study demonstrated three independent copies of chromosome 8 in 26 of 30 metaphases. FISH studies (using probes MYC and D8Z2) confirmed trisomy 8 in 76.7% of metaphases and 87.0% of interphase nuclei from a PHA-stimulated culture as well as 74.5% of interphase nuclei from a direct unstimulated preparation.

Name.ElementValue: Morphological abnormality of the central nervous system

ClinicalAssertion.StudyDescription: Copy number variation identified through the course of routine clinical cytogenomic testing in postnatal populations, with clinical assertions as classified by the original submitter.
